rathon, Monday 15 April 2013. Photograph: Wang Lei/Xinhua Press/Corbis")))) ("Transformers 4 mounts reality TV search for Chinese wannabe actors" "<div class=\"track\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://hits.guardian.co.uk/b/ss/guardiangu-feeds/1/H.25.4/71312?ns=guardian&pageName=Article%3Atransformers-4-reality-tv-china%3A1896317&ch=Film&c3=GU.co.uk&c4=Action+and+adventure+%28Film+genre%29%2CScience+fiction+and+fantasy+%28Film+genre%29%2CMichael+Bay%2CMark+Wahlberg%2CFilm%2CParamount+Pictures%2CReality+TV+%28TV+genre%29%2CTelevision+%28Culture%29%2CCulture%2CChina+%28News%29%2CAsia+Pacific+%28News%29%2CWorld+news&c5=Unclassified%2CNot+commercially+useful%2CTelevision+Media%2CFilm+Reviews&c6=Ben+Child&c7=2013%2F04%2F19+11%3A59&c8=1896317&c9=Article&c10=News&c13=&c19=GUK&c47=UK&c64=UK&c65=Transformers+4+mounts+reality+TV+search+for+Chinese+wannabe+actors&c66=Culture&c72=&c73=&c74=&c75=&h2=GU%2FCulture%2FFilm%2FAction+and+adventure\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" /></div><p class=\"standfirst\">Michael Bay's robot franchise capitalises on popularity in China with reality TV recruitment show</p><p>Transformers 4, the latest instalment in <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/film/michael-bay\" title=\"\">Michael Bay</a>'s interminable giant robot saga, is to recruit four Chinese actors <a href=\"http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/transformers-4-paramount-cast-chinese-441636\" title=\"\">via a reality TV talent search</a>.</p><p><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/feedarticle/10728706\" title=\"\">Studio Paramount announced earlier this month</a> that the film will be a US-Chinese co-production, a nod to the franchise's huge popularity in China. Recent instalment <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/film/movie/140386/transformers\" title=\"\">Transformers: Dark of the Moon</a> stands as the fourth-highest-grossing film ever in China with a haul of $165m (£108m) in 2011.</p><p></p><p>Transformers 4 Chinese Actor Talent Search was launched at a press conference in Beijing this week. US judges will include Transformers producer Lorenzo DiBonaventura and former Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences chief Sid Ganis, who now chairs Jiaflix Enterprises, a partner production company on the film.</p><p></p><p>Ganis said the show would \"give actors and fans of the Transformers franchise the opportunity to appear in a major motion picture, and it will provide the world audience yet another glimpse of the Chinese people, the Chinese culture and China itself\".</p><p>Judges are hoping to find two trained actors and two with no previous on-screen experience to join other Chinese cast members for the film. Local judges will include representatives from Transformers 4's Chinese co-producers, China Movie Channel, and the website where wannabe contestants can register for the show.</p><p></p><p><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/film/2012/nov/09/mark-wahlberg-transformers-4\" title=\"\">Mark Wahlberg is the lead</a> in the new movie, having replaced <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/film/shia-labeouf\" title=\"\">Shia LaBeouf</a>. Bay announced in November that the star of Boogie Nights and The Departed had been given the role following a successful stint on his forthcoming bodybuilding-themed action comedy Pain & Gain.</p><div class=\"related\" style=\"float: left; margin-right: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;\"><ul><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/film/actionandadventure\">Action and adventure</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/film/sciencefictionandfantasy\">Science fiction and fantasy</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/film/michael-bay\">Michael Bay</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/film/mark-wahlberg\">Mark Wahlberg</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/film/paramount-pictures\">Paramount Pictures</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/tv-and-radio/reality-tv\">Reality TV</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/culture/television\">Television</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/china\">China</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/asia-pacific\">Asia Pacific</a></li></ul></div><div class=\"author\"><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/profile/benchild\">Ben Child</a></div><br/><div class=\"terms\"><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk\">guardian.co.uk</a> &copy; 2013 Guardian News and Media Limited or its affiliated companies. All rights reserved. | Use of this content is subject to our <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/help/terms-of-service\">Terms & Conditions</a> | <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/help/feeds\">More Feeds</a></div><p style=\"clear:both\" />" "http://www.guardian.co.uk/film/2013/apr/19/transformers-4-reality-tv-china" (20849 9089) old 17 nil nil ((title nil "Transformers 4 mounts reality TV search for Chinese wannabe actors") (link nil "http://www.guardian.co.uk/film/2013/apr/19/transformers-4-reality-tv-china") (description nil "<div class=\"track\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://hits.guardian.co.uk/b/ss/guardiangu-feeds/1/H.25.4/71312?ns=guardian&pageName=Article%3Atransformers-4-reality-tv-china%3A1896317&ch=Film&c3=GU.co.uk&c4=Action+and+adventure+%28Film+genre%29%2CScience+fiction+and+fantasy+%28Film+genre%29%2CMichael+Bay%2CMark+Wahlberg%2CFilm%2CParamount+Pictures%2CReality+TV+%28TV+genre%29%2CTelevision+%28Culture%29%2CCulture%2CChina+%28News%29%2CAsia+Pacific+%28News%29%2CWorld+news&c5=Unclassified%2CNot+commercially+useful%2CTelevision+Media%2CFilm+Reviews&c6=Ben+Child&c7=2013%2F04%2F19+11%3A59&c8=1896317&c9=Article&c10=News&c13=&c19=GUK&c47=UK&c64=UK&c65=Transformers+4+mounts+reality+TV+search+for+Chinese+wannabe+actors&c66=Culture&c72=&c73=&c74=&c75=&h2=GU%2FCulture%2FFilm%2FAction+and+adventure\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" /></div><p class=\"standfirst\">Michael Bay's robot franchise capitalises on popularity in China with reality TV recruitment show</p><p>Transformers 4, the latest instalment in <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/film/michael-bay\" title=\"\">Michael Bay</a>'s interminable giant robot saga, is to recruit four Chinese actors <a href=\"http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/transformers-4-paramount-cast-chinese-441636\" title=\"\">via a reality TV talent search</a>.</p><p><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/feedarticle/10728706\" title=\"\">Studio Paramount announced earlier this month</a> that the film will be a US-Chinese co-production, a nod to the franchise's huge popularity in China. Recent instalment <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/film/movie/140386/transformers\" title=\"\">Transformers: Dark of the Moon</a> stands as the fourth-highest-grossing film ever in China with a haul of $165m (£108m) in 2011.</p><p></p><p>Transformers 4 Chinese Actor Talent Search was launched at a press conference in Beijing this week. US judges will include Transformers producer Lorenzo DiBonaventura and former Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences chief Sid Ganis, who now chairs Jiaflix Enterprises, a partner production company on the film.</p><p></p><p>Ganis said the show would \"give actors and fans of the Transformers franchise the opportunity to appear in a major motion picture, and it will provide the world audience yet another glimpse of the Chinese people, the Chinese culture and China itself\".</p><p>Judges are hoping to find two trained actors and two with no previous on-screen experience to join other Chinese cast members for the film. Local judges will include representatives from Transformers 4's Chinese co-producers, China Movie Channel, and the website where wannabe contestants can register for the show.</p><p></p><p><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/film/2012/nov/09/mark-wahlberg-transformers-4\" title=\"\">Mark Wahlberg is the lead</a> in the new movie, having replaced <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/film/shia-labeouf\" title=\"\">Shia LaBeouf</a>. Bay announced in November that the star of Boogie Nights and The Departed had been given the role following a successful stint on his forthcoming bodybuilding-themed action comedy Pain & Gain.</p><div class=\"related\" style=\"float: left; margin-right: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;\"><ul><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/film/actionandadventure\">Action and adventure</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/film/sciencefictionandfantasy\">Science fiction and fantasy</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/film/michael-bay\">Michael Bay</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/film/mark-wahlberg\">Mark Wahlberg</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/film/paramount-pictures\">Paramount Pictures</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/tv-and-radio/reality-tv\">Reality TV</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/culture/television\">Television</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/china\">China</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/asia-pacific\">Asia Pacific</a></li></ul></div><div class=\"author\"><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/profile/benchild\">Ben Child</a></div><br/><div class=\"terms\"><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk\">guardian.co.uk</a> &copy; 2013 Guardian News and Media Limited or its affiliated companies. All rights reserved. | Use of this content is subject to our <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/help/terms-of-service\">Terms & Conditions</a> | <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/help/feeds\">More Feeds</a></div><p style=\"clear:both\" />") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/film")) "Action and adventure") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/film")) "Science fiction and fantasy") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/film")) "Michael Bay") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/film")) "Mark Wahlberg") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/film")) "Film") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/film")) "Paramount Pictures") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/tv-and-radio")) "Reality TV") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/tv-and